Function transform_text(text, format):
    Initialize an empty list to hold the transformed values

    For each character in the text:
        Get the ASCII value of the character

        If the format is "Hex":
            Convert the ASCII value to a hexadecimal string
            Add the hexadecimal string to the list, prefixed with "0x"

        Else if the format is "Binary":
            Convert the ASCII value to a binary string
            Add the binary string to the list, prefixed with "0b"

    Join the list of transformed values into a single string with spaces between them

    Return the resulting string

Function character_to_hex(character):
    ascii_value = get_ascii_value(character)  // Convert character to its ASCII value
    hex_value = convert_to_hex(ascii_value)  // Convert ASCII value to hexadecimal string
    Return hex_value
